I've been racking my brain for a while trying to figure out what all of these stories have in common as the glue of what makes this community like the old and effectively now dead monster girl community (but less shit since monster girls are shit). I've finally realized it after looking at the pictures that people have gotten but especially this one picture I see posted every once in a while. It's acceptance.

HMoFA from the very conception is accepting of differences and what you are. You're a human and you aren't a furboi or whatever, that cannot be changed and the context of the story still remain that you are writing a traditional HMoFA story. It's like the difference between a cyborg and an android. One starts off human and remains human until you replace all of the meat with metal, and the other was never human to begin with and lacks the spark of inherent humanity. The stories are generally about someone who is outside of the norm of what the lady might be used to, and she's outside of his as well. The shocking stories here like HYSTN and the rape rabbit series feature twists on the acceptance. Accepting being forced into the role of being a father in the rapey rabbit series, and acceptance that the two star crossed lovers on the battlefield can't be together forever.
